- phase 1: basic kernel
    - add memory management (gdt, ldt)
    - add a user interface (cli)
    - add a basic file system (maybe fat32?)
    - add device management (keyboard, mouse?)

- phase 2: getting into userspace
    - add ability to run userspace apps (isolated memory space)
    - add a scheduler
    - add basic system calls (like printf)
    - add IPC
    - add ability to load kernel modules

- phase 3: networking
    - add ethernet drivers
    - add network stack (tcp/ip)
    - add http(s) support
    - add ability to set/get ip
    - add ability to ping

- phase 4: gui
    - let's see!
